*inlining* the erms case might show that nicely in<br />&gt; profiles.<br /><br />Side note: the fact that Jens' patch (which I don't like in that form)<br />allegedly shrunk the resulting kernel binary would seem to indicate<br />that there's a *lot* of compile-time constant-sized memcpy calls that<br />we are missing, and that fall back to copy_user_generic().<br /><br />It might be interesting to just change raw_copy_to/from_user() to<br />handle a lot more cases (in particular, handle cases where 'size' is<br />8-byte aligned). The special cases we *do* have may not be the right<br />ones (the 10-byte case in particular looks odd).<br /><br />For example, instead of having a "if constant size is 8 bytes, do one<br />get/put_user()" case, we might have a "if constant size is &lt; 64 just<br />unroll it into get/put_user()" calls.<br /><br />                  Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
